# C++ Standard Version

## Requirement

All C++ projects SHALL use the latest available C++ standard version supported by the compiler.

Compiler flags SHALL explicitly specify the C++ standard version (e.g., `-std=c++23`, `-std=c++20`).

CMake projects SHALL set `CMAKE_CXX_STANDARD` to the latest available standard version.

